---
import InstallBlock from './InstallBlock.astro';
import { quickstart } from '../config';

// Closing CTA: tagline, one line of copy, and the install repeated. This is
// also the page's #quickstart target, so the hero's "Quick start" link and the
// footer both land here. W-3 lives on this block, not the hero one: it is the
// exact quickstart from config.ts (start-from-a-prompt demo).
---

<section id="quickstart" class="cta">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Never ship a board your docs no longer describe.</h2>

      <p class="lede">
        copperhead is open source and free to use. Install once, describe the
        board you want in a short <code>brief.md</code>, and run <code>create</code>.
      </p>

      <div class="install">
        <InstallBlock lines={quickstart} />
      </div>

      <!-- What `--brief brief.md` points at. Content grounded in the Open
           Telegraph brief (usecase-copperhead.md): ESP32-S3, BLE HID, the 25 µA
           sleep budget, the 3.5 mm key jack. -->
      <figure class="brief">
        <figcaption>brief.md</figcaption>
        <pre><code>{`# Pocket Morse key

A pocket-size Morse key that types over Bluetooth as a standard keyboard.

- ESP32-S3, BLE HID
- Li-Po cell, USB-C charging
- Sleep current budget: 25 µA
- 3.5 mm jack for an external paddle`}</code></pre>
      </figure>

      <p class="footnote">
        Requires Node 20+ and kicad-cli. The agent refuses to run on a dirty git
        tree, refuses edits without a validated proposal, and refuses changes that
        break your documented budgets. You will come to like being told no.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  /* Closing CTA sits inside the mastra card, so the section itself carries no
     divider — the 2px frame provides the separation. */
  .cta .wrap {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .card {
    border: 2px solid #1c1c1c;
    background: #0a0a0a;
    border-radius: 20px;
    padding: clamp(44px, 6vw, 88px) clamp(24px, 5vw, 72px);
  }

  h2 {
    /* mastra headline-2xl, matching the section titles elsewhere */
    font-size: clamp(1.875rem, 3.8vw, 3.375rem);
    max-width: 22ch;
    margin-inline: auto;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }

  .lede {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    max-width: 52ch;
    margin: 1.35rem auto 0;
  }

  .lede code {
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .install {
    max-width: 42rem;
    margin: 2.5rem auto 0;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .brief {
    max-width: 42rem;
    margin: 0.75rem auto 0;
    text-align: left;
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .brief figcaption {
    padding: 10px 24px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }

  .brief pre {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 18px 24px;
    /* wraps instead of scrolling: unlike the shell lines above, nothing here
       needs to stay on one line, and this is what keeps the block compact on
       mobile */
    white-space: pre-wrap;
    overflow-wrap: break-word;
  }

  .brief code {
    display: block;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .lede {
      font-size: 1.02rem;
    }

    .brief figcaption {
      padding: 8px 16px;
    }

    .brief pre {
      padding: 14px 16px;
    }
  }

  .footnote {
    margin: 1.75rem auto 0;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 58ch;
  }
</style>
